transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Olivia speaking, who do I have the pleasure of speaking with today?

Speaker 2: My name's Alan.

Speaker 1: Hi Alan, how are you?

Speaker 2: I'm fine, you?

Speaker 1: Good.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: I wanted to cancel my order, so I just wanted to try this, and all of a sudden I received another prescription in the mail and getting charged 60 plus something dollars, so I just want to cancel it.

Speaker 2: Yeah, I can definitely look into this for you.

Speaker 1: Okay, what is your date of birth, Alan?

Speaker 2: 3-25-70.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Okay, that's not what we have, but I'll update it.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 1: 6-2-1-9, Tarragona, T-A-R-R-A-G-O-N-A, drive, San Diego, California, 9-2-1-1-5.

Speaker 2: Great, perfect.

Speaker 1: Yeah, so I see your prescription here.

Speaker 2: All right, well, yeah, I mean, if you don't want to receive regular refills with your prescription, you certainly don't have to.

Speaker 1: You always have the option to place your prescription on hold for up to six months, just because six months is when the prescription would expire if we didn't refill it, and the way that would work is if you did want to order at any point before then you could, you just have to give us a call to place the order yourself.

Speaker 2: Okay, sounds great.

Speaker 1: Okay, great.

Speaker 2: So, yeah, if you need anything before July 27th, just give us a call at this number, Monday through Friday, 8-5 Pacific, we're always here.

Speaker 1: Okay, so as of now, I'm canceled, correct, or on hold, or whatever you want to call it?

Speaker 2: Yeah, the prescription's on hold, but it's still available to you, but if you need anything in these next six months, you can have it, you just have to call us to place the order because the prescription has been placed on hold for you.

Speaker 1: Sounds awesome.

Speaker 2: Thank you so much.

Speaker 1: Yeah, thank you.

Speaker 2: I hope you have a great day.

Speaker 1: You too.

Speaker 2: Bye.
